data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
This little tool uses two methods to reduce VRAM usage: Meshes: This makes the lowest LOD meshes unavailable for the rendering engine. Side effects can be most notably: a reduced viewing distance (depending on the setting) and some graphical glitches.
Textures: This method is a bit more sophisticated as it removes textures' mipmaps with the highest resolution and repacks them into the game's .dat files. Each quality step halfs their resolution, if possible.
